==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[conscientia]]'' 'knowledge winin oneself', from ''[[scire]]'' 'to know'.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/kɒnʃɛns/
*{{audio|en-us-conscience.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''conscience'''
# A person's [[moral]] [[sense]] of [[right]] and [[wrong]], chiefly as it affects their own behaviour.

